# SSL Day 5 â€“ Groups & Role-Based Access Control (RBAC)

## Objective
Implemented role-based access control using Active Directory security groups for file access and Remote Desktop login.

## Work Completed
- Created security groups for staff access and RDP
- Assigned domain users to groups
- Applied NTFS permissions to groups (no direct user permissions)
- Granted Remote Desktop access via group membership
- Verified domain login and access from CLIENT01

## Skills Demonstrated
- Active Directory group management
- Role-Based Access Control (RBAC)
- NTFS permission configuration
- Remote Desktop Services access control
- Domain authentication verification

